article.headline: San Francisco 72, Montana 71
article.story: MISSOULA (AP) -- James Bayless had 22 points and 13 rebounds Saturday as the San Francisco Dons held off Montana 72-71. USF (4-4) led 72-67 as the clock wound under four seconds, but Andre Hazel fouled Montana's Roy Booker as Booker went up for a 3-point shot. Booker made the first two free throws with 3.6 seconds left to cut the lead to 72-69, then intentionally missed the third. The Grizzlies (3-3) tapped the rebound out to Derrick Mansell, but Mansell stepped toward the basket rather than behind the 3-point line before nailing a 16-foot shot at the buzzer. The Dons, who have only played one of their first eight games at home, led most of the way, including a 35-30 halftime lead. Kevin Criswell's 3-pointer at the 8:50 mark started a 16-8 run by the Grizzlies, and Kamarr Davis' two free throws with 2:11 remaining cut the lead to 62-60. But the Dons made six straight free throws, four by Jason Gaines, to pull ahead 68-60 with 43 seconds to go. Gaines, who scored 10 points, was 7 of 8 on foul shots in the final 1:57. Criswell led Montana with 16 points and Booker had 13. The Dons, who outrebounded the Grizzlies 42-32, also got 10 points and 10 rebounds from Tyrone Riley.
